b'To bring joy to people\xe2\x80\x99s hearts, fun to their lives and smiles to. Thanks to all who contributed their gifts and talents. A Beautiful Revolution Pt. 2 is out now: https://t.co/BtgXa41ivj'

b'How could this music be an example of the beautiful aspects of revolution that include joy, self-love, compassion, dreams, peace and good times? As a piece of art, I believe we took it to different places musically only to come back to the original intention.'

b'more appreciation for my family, friends and the simple things in life. I wanted to write about that and create music that embodied that. What does a new day, a brighter day feel like being told through an emcee and some gifted musicians?'

b'There was still hurt, anger and pain lingering, so I was thinking, \xe2\x80\x9cwhat is the next step in this revolution?\xe2\x80\x9d I thought about what being still in these times had brought me and that was a peace beyond understanding, a greater love for self, a closer connection with God, and...'

b'A Beautiful Revolution Pt. 2 was created with hope and inspiration in mind. The spirit of the album was meant to emulate what a greater day would sound and feel like. We were in the midst of some tough political and socially challenging times. https://t.co/72tQRuD8gJ'

b'During your healing process with your trauma, practice patience and self-compassion. #QueenSugarTalks'
b'We are not defined by our trauma. We all suffer. We all experience trauma. #QueenSugarTalks'
b'It takes exponentially more strength to be vulnerable than it does to avoid and run from your trauma. Being silent about your pain is not a sign of strength. #QueenSugarTalks'
b'To be vulnerable and open about our trauma is to be deeply courageous. It takes great strength to be vulnerable. #QueenSugarTalks'
b'Your trauma can be turned into your strength but only with hard work and dedication to addressing the issue head on. #QueenSugarTalks'

b'If men saw love for the source of strength that it is, there would be so much healing and so much suffering alleviated from millions of people\xe2\x80\x99s lives. Love gives us the courage to have an honest confrontation with the root causes of our pain. #QueenSugarTalks https://t.co/eZw9mJTfMy'
b'As men, we have to view love, empathy and compassion as strengths and tools for our arsenal in healing our trauma. We must practice self-love and self-compassion as we heal. #QueenSugarTalks'
